text:
1. All Animals, Cows, Chickens, Pigs, Fish and Lambs are sentient beings like you, they possess a brain, can feel different emotions such as fear, distress, joy and guilt, they feel physical pain and have a preference to live. No different from us.

2. Over a Billion land and marine animals are unnaturally bred into existence each year for the sole purpose of being tortured and murdered unnecessarily for the Meat, Dairy, Egg and Wool Industry. They are murdered in “humane” ways – bolt gun to the head, slit to their throat, gas chamber etc.

3. Dairy Industry: In order for a female cow to produce milk like a human woman she has to give birth. So the female cow is forcibly impregnated by a farmer thrusting his/her arm into her anus to loosen the area and injects her with bull semen (this is what you call BEASTILITY), then when she is pregnant her calf is taken away from her as she cries out for days in search for her baby. Male calves are murdered instantly as they are seen as useless while female calves go through the same cycle as their mother. This cycle of forced pregnancy continues again and again and again until either the female cow becomes ill, weak or unable to produce so she then goes to the meat industry to be murdered. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UcN7SGGoCNI

4. Egg Industry: A similar process occurs with Chickens and when chickens feel emotional stress because of their conditions they self-harm so a farmer removes their beaks. When chickens are forcibly impregnated to lay eggs the male chicks are thrown into a grinder while alive as they are seen as useless while female chicks go through the same process. Turkeys and Chickens are fattened up so much that their own legs break due to their weight.

5. Do not compare Animals to Plants. Plants are NOT sentient beings, they do not possess a brain, do not feel emotion and do not have a central nervous system so DO NOT FEEL PAIN.

6. Health:  consuming Animals, Dairy and Egg causes the following illnesses and diseases and more. Cardiovascular disease like Heart disease (from clogged arteries), Type 2 Diabetes, Osteoporosis (from dairy), Colon Cancer, Breast Cancer, Prostate Cancer and Obesity. They are all high in saturated fat and highly acidic. Cholesterol is only found in animal products (including egg and dairy) which are all very high in it. We can be healthy on a vegan diet - all calcium, protein, iron and all other minerals, vitamins and good fats come from plant-based diet. The largest nutrition organisations such as the British and American Associations have confirmed this.

7. Environment: Animal agriculture is destroying the planet. It is one of the largest causes of greenhouse gases. http://www.cowspiracy.com/facts/

8. Poverty: Animal agriculture is the leading cause of poverty around the world. We are taking billions of plants, destroying rainforests, and taking gallons of water from developing countries to feed billions of animals in the Meat, Dairy and Egg Industry to be consumed by people from developed countries.

Morality: We are exploiting these animals to be consumed, tested on and we wear their skins just because we feel we can, because they are weaker, they are in a different shape and form, they do not speak human language, they are not as intelligent as us and because society says it is okay to.

If the law makes it acceptable it does not make it right. Slavery of humans at one point was too acceptable. Intelligence does not make it acceptable otherwise it is justified for us to murder autistic children. Taste/pleasure does not make it justified otherwise it is justified for rapists and serial murderers to do what they do. And it is not personal preference when your personal preference has A VICTIM. SEE IT FROM THE VICTIM’S POSITION, NOT YOUR OWN.

After being aware of all these points, it’s your responsibility, if you claim to be a moral human to walk the right path or continue walking on the wrong path blindly and immorally believing it to be right.

text:
Eating a predator is unhealthy? Any animal we eat will be a predator of another animal. Our biology has not evolved our bodies to be on top of the food chain. In fact we are more herbivorous than omnivorous. We do not possess claws and fangs like omnivores, we do not have small intestine like omnivores, we don’t have a strong stomach acid type like omnivores and we do not possess omnivorous instincts. Our biology only matches herbivores. In addition, consuming animals, dairy and egg causes the following diseases in humans: cardiovascular disease like Heart disease (from clogged arteries), Type 2 Diabetes, Osteoporosis (from dairy), Colon Cancer, Breast Cancer, Prostate Cancer and Obesity. Again, our biology has not been made to handle animal consumption.

This statement of being a part of and top of the food chain is a fallacy made up by humans to overlook and avoid moral decisions by claiming our actions have been predetermined by our "biology". We have alternative ways to be healthy so shouldn't we be using that intelligence you are talking about to make moral decisions and not oppress other sentient beings unnecessarily just because they are in a different shape and form, even though that are sentient like us.

Consumption of animals is unhealthy for us, we are herbivores pretending to be omnivores and we are not even part of the food chain so why would you still feel you need to eat sentient beings?﻿
